TY  - JOUR
TI  - Three-Stage Least-Squares and Full Maximum Likelihood Estimates
AU  - Sargan, J. D.
AB  - [This paper proves in the context of maximum likelihood estimation of linear stochastic models of the Cowles Commission type [2], that if the model is fully identified and stable and the error variance matrix unrestricted, three-stage least-squares estimates differ asymptotically from full maximum likelihood estimates by order 1/T, where T is the number of time periods. When the full maximum likelihood estimates are best asymptotic normal so are the three-stage least-squares estimates.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan. - Apr., 1964
